Nigeria’s Super Falcons have arrived in Leon State of Guanajuato, Mexico for the four-nation invitational tournament tagged, Revelation Cup. The Players have settled down in the City and held a recovery session on Tuesday. The team will train on grass later today ahead of their opening match. Randy Waldrum’s side will take on hosts Mexico in their first game on Wednesday night. Kick-off is 10pm Nigeria time. On Saturday, the former African champions will be up against Colombia in their second game. Kick-off is 7pm Nigeria time. The Nigerian ladies will round up their campaign against Costa Rica on Tuesday, February 21. That game will start at 7pm Nigeria time. The four countries will use the competition to prepare for the 2023 FIFA Women’s World Cup. The Super Falcons will also participate in another invitational tournament in Turkey in April.